Question: Develop an argument for or against the following statement: television violence is appropriate for audiences of all ages
Answer:
While I'm not a proponent of censorship, I think that children should be monitored in what they watch. Television now is not the same as it was twenty years ago. Violence in particular is much more vivid. When impressionable minds see these things, they learn from them. I am not qualified to say that all children repeat whatever they see on televion, nor do I believe that. But young minds are particularly malleable, and we should be wary of what we put into them.